## Full Worked Example: 5 Phases

```
                     Phase 1         Phase 2      Phase 3    Phase 4        Phase 5
Timeline:  ──────────────────────── ──────────── ────────── ────────── ──────────────
Days:      1        40       80      81    89     90   95    96   100
           │─────────┼────────┤      │─────┤      │────┤     │────┤
           │  A + B  │  A + B │      │ B   │      │A+B │     │A+B │
           │connected│        │      │only │      │    │     │    │
```

| Day | Active Camps | Daily Cost (cached) | Ref Count | Cost/Ref | Notes |
|-----|-------------|-------------------|-----------|----------|-------|
| 50  | A + B       | 45K + 32K = 77K   | 40        | 1,925    | Normal operation |
| 79  | A + B       | 51K + 28K = 79K   | 45        | 1,756    | Last day before disconnect |
| **80** | **A + B** | **48K + 33K = 81K** | **42** | **1,929** | **A disconnected at end of day** |
| 81  | B only      | 35K               | 44        | 795      | Cost drops (correct! A isn't spending) |
| 85  | B only      | 31K               | 38        | 816      | Gap period — only B's real spend |
| 89  | B only      | 29K               | 41        | 707      | Last gap day |
| **90** | **A + B** | **52K + 34K = 86K** | **43** | **2,000** | **A reconnected** |
| 95  | A + B       | 47K + 30K = 77K   | 39        | 1,974    | Back to normal |

> [!TIP]
> Notice: Day 50's cost (77K) **NEVER changes** regardless of what happens on Day 80 or Day 90. This is the key difference from the broken totals approach.

