## Summary: The 3 Layers

```
Layer 1: DAILY CACHE (immutable facts)
  "Campaign A spent 45,000 VND on Jan 15"
  → Comes from Google Ads API
  → Never changes, even if campaign is disconnected
  → Like a bank statement: the money was spent, period.

Layer 2: LEDGER (immutable events)
  "Campaign A was connected to Project Y on Jan 1"
  "Campaign A was disconnected from Project Y on Mar 15"
  → Determines ATTRIBUTION: which project "owns" each day's cost
  → Like stock transfer records: who held the shares on each date

Layer 3: DERIVED METRICS (calculated on-the-fly)
  "Project Y's cost on Jan 15 = Camp A (45K) + Camp B (32K) = 77K"
  → JOIN of Layer 1 × Layer 2, clamped to date range
  → Like portfolio valuation: derived from holdings × market data
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **The key insight**: Disconnecting a campaign doesn't change history. It only changes the FUTURE. 
> 
> Just like selling a stock doesn't change the dividends you already earned while holding it.
